The stock market rose on Wednesday for the second consecutive day as Nestle Nigeria Plc and 19 others gained at the end of trading on the floor of the Nigerian Exchange Limited. Nestle saw its share price jump by 10 per cent to N1,540. Other top gainers were Ikeja Hotel Plc, Oando Plc, LASACO Assurance Plc and Berger Paints Nigeria Plc. Fourteen companies recorded price losses at the end of trading, led by B.O.C Gases Plc, which lost 10 per cent to close at N8.55 per share. Sovereign Trust Insurance Plc followed with a 7.14 per cent loss, ending the day at N0.26 per share. Other top losers were PZ Cussons Nigeria Plc, Regal Insurance Plc and Champion Breweries Plc. The NGX All-Share Index, which tracks all the listed equities on the exchange, rose by 0.71 per cent to 37,907.28 basis points from 37,640.75bps on Tuesday. The market capitalisation increased from N19.62tn on Tuesday to N19.76tn on Wednesday. A total of 213.70 million shares valued at N3.23bn were traded on the floor of the NGX in 3,522 deals. Wema Bank shares were the most traded in terms of volume at 18.31 million shares, followed by Oando Plc at 15.62 million shares and Mortgage Benefits Assurance Plc at 15.10 million shares. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com